Comment: homeworkouts101 said "-
â–ªï¸Weighted T-Push Ups
-
TARGETS
1âƒ£Chest
2âƒ£Shoulders
3âƒ£Core
4âƒ£Glutes -
â–ªï¸Grab a pair of dumbbells and place them where your hands would normally go when performing a push-up. The dumbbells should be slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Grasp the dumbbells and set yourself in a push-up position with arms straight. Palms should be facing each other. This is the starting position. Begin exercise by lowering yourself down until your chest nearly touches the ground. Pause, then as you push yourself back up, lift your right arm up as you rotate your body to the right. Rotate all the way over until your arm is straight up and your left side is facing the ground. Your body will now look like a "T" on its side. Reverse movements back to starting position. This completes one rep. Repeat on opposite side."

Comment: gymworkouts101 said "-
â–ªï¸Tricep Pushdowns (With V Bar Attachment)
-
TARGETS
1âƒ£Triceps - Standing upright with the torso straight and a very small inclination forward, bring the upper arms close to your body and perpendicular to the floor. The forearms should be pointing up towards the pulley as they hold the bar. This is your starting position. Using the triceps, bring the V- bar down until it touches the front of your thighs and the arms are fully extended perpendicular to the floor. The upper arms should always remain stationary next to your torso and only the forearms should move. Exhale as you perform this movement. After a second hold at the contracted position, bring the bar slowly up to the starting point. Breathe in as you perform this step."

Comment: gymworkouts101 said "-
â–ªï¸Leg Extensions
-
TARGETS
1âƒ£Quads
â–ªï¸- This exercise you will need to use a leg extension machine. First choose your weight and sit on the machine with your legs under the pad (feet pointed forward) and the hands holding the side bars. This will be your starting position.  Tip: You will need to adjust the pad so that it falls on top of your lower leg (just above your feet). Also, make sure that your legs form a 90-degree angle between the lower and upper leg. If the angle is less than 90-degrees then that means the knee is over the toes which in turn creates undue stress at the knee joint. If the machine is designed that way, either look for another machine or just make sure that when you start executing the exercise you stop going down once you hit the 90-degree angle. Using your quadriceps, extend your legs to the maximum as you exhale. Ensure that the rest of the body remains stationary on the seat. Pause a second on the contracted position. Slowly lower the weight back to the original position as you inhale, ensuring that you do not go past the 90-degree angle limit."

Comment: coachbueno said "DIM

DIM (diindolylmethane) is a phytonutrient found in cruciferous vegetables like cabbage, broccoli, Brussels sprouts, cauliflower, and kale. It helps resolving estrogen imbalance by preventing either its drastic increase or decrease. In women, DIM helps maintain testosterone in its active free form which promotes a healthy libido, good mood, and eases PMS symptoms.

Recent studies from the Nutritional Sciences Department at the University of California at Berkeley have shown that DIM has anti-proliferative effects on prostate cancer cells and on human mammary tumor cells. It also has unique immune modulatory properties.

If you have any questions, talk to an expert!"

2-3 haas avocados 
1 juice of a lemon and lime 
1/4 chopped up white onions 
2 cloves of garlic, minced
1/2 teaspoon of salt, pepper and cummin 
1 tablespoon of chopped cilantro 
Mash avocados in a bowl with a fork. Fold in onions, garlic and lime juice. Season with salt, pepper and cummin and then finish with lemon juice to keep guac from browning to quickly. Garnish with cilantro and for extra heat add some chopped jalapeÃ±o ðŸ’"

Comment: yana_yoga said "I have been out of practice for 3 weeks now due to a fractured wrist. This is the first time ever my body is forcing me to take a break. The effects are surfacing in a hurricane that I could not even predict. I have less patience, I am short-tempered, I am closed off, I experience weird insecurities and am not present as I usually am in even simple daily tasks, but best of all, I am able to recognize it all. Comment: yogawithmii said "Day 4 of the #2ndSeries March #Yoga Challenge with @yogiyanni_ & @yogawithmii, sponsored by @yogiiza & @splurgejuicecafe.

How about that first posture of Second Series, #yogis?
For me, that has always been one of the hardest parts of the #practice.
Just have in mind that different asanas will prove easier for some and more difficult for others. 
But I'm #excited to see how everybody's trying their best.

Let's continue with the #challenge, and go to the second #pose of the #Ashtanga Intermediate Series, KrouncÄsana. An interesting position that challenges the flexibility both in the hips as well as the legs.
This #asana requires a lot of patience due to all the things that must be engaged and released at the same time. A very good example of how in #yoga the body works in synergistic ways contracting and relaxing different muscle groups as the same time.

Getting into it can be done through a basic jump or walk through from Down Dog, or a more advanced floating #transition directly into the ready position.
In either case, one leg will be bent at the knee and pointing back, and the opposite leg will be raised and fully extended, ideally with both hands binding in front of the top foot.
Once there, we try to bring the chin to the shin of that raised leg, while pulling the leg towards the torso and maintaining the spine extended as much as possible.
After holding that position for 5 breaths, extend the arms to make room for jumping or walking back to Chaturanga Dandasana.
Then do the same process on the other side.
The #balance between strength and flexibility that's needed for executing each posture will come over time.
Stay disciplined and trust the process.

In this demonstration I'm showing only one side, go check @yogiyanni_ for his version of Heron Posture.

You can post a video or a photo of the posture without worrying about perfect form, just approximate as much as possible.
But most importantly, have #fun and show us how creative you can get with this.

Be sure to include the hashtag #2ndSeries as well as @yogiyanni_, @yogawithmii, @yogiiza & @splurgejuicecafe on each one of your posts.

Shanti à¥ : )
ðŸŽ¶ DJ Drez"

Comment: fitness_dishes said "*Brownie Pancakes*

Dry ingredients:
Â½ cup flour of choice (I use combo of oat and whole wheat pastry)
Â½ cup unsweetened cocoa powder
1 tablespoon baking powder
2 tablespoons granulated sweetener of choice

Wet ingredients:
â…“ cup unsweetened almond milk
1 egg
Â¼ cup unsweetened applesauce
1 teaspoon vanilla

Method:
1. In a large bowl, sift together the dry ingredients; set aside.
2. In a smaller bowl, mix together the wet ingredients; set aside. 
3. Add wet to dry and mix with a fork to keep it airy. (Batter will be incredibly thick.) Let it rest as you preheat your pan.
4. Preheat nonstick skillet over medium heat. Spray with cooking spray. 
5. Lay dollops of batter on the pan, let cook for 30 seconds, then add a little more batter (this makes them real fluffy). 6. Fry for 1Â½-2 minutes on each side.

Comment: kenouniverse said "Rare and beautiful pink stalactite necklace! Stalactites are formed at the roof of a cave and begin with one drop of mineral-rich water!

When the drop falls, it leaves behind the thinnest ring of calcite. Each subsequent drop that forms and falls deposits another ring. Over time, these rings build to create a stunning column of minerals.

Stalactite is associated with hidden inner growth, secret expansion of the higher self."

Comment: yogawithmii said "Aesthetic (Arts, yoga, sports, etc.)
An experience in which your senses are operating at their peak, when you're present in the current moment, when you're resonating with the excitement of this thing that you're experiencing, when you are fully alive.

Anesthetic
An experience in which your senses are shut off, and you deaden yourself to what's happening.

Try to make your life more about being present and enjoying the moment.
When you #practice #yoga, you train the body and mind to become hyper focused and stay in the "zone".

Comment: coachbueno said "Is it ok to drink alcohol?
What are the consequences? Does it interfere with my diet and physical activities?
Learn about it.
Overdose is the name we use to describe the ingestion of substances in large doses resulting in a toxic state. If you drink too much alcohol, you will most likely feel depressed or euphoric; you might vomit and feel dizzy, among other symptoms.
Felling dizzy, having a headache and dry mouth, and lacking energy are the symptoms you may feel when you are hungover. It is your body reacting to the high ingestion of alcohol. 40 mg of alcohol per 100ml of blood is enough to create this euphoric state causing discomfort the next day.
Alcohol poisoning is the next step. In this case, the person has to be hospitalized, take insulin injections, have a gastric lavage, and other treatments that may vary according to the poisoning. 300 mg of alcohol per 100 ml of blood can lead to this situation. A more severe poisoning case can cause death by overdose (around 500 mg per 100ml).
Excessive and prolonged alcohol consumption may cause the inflammation of the lining of the stomach, which is called gastritis. This causes a lot of discomfort to the individual including burning or a gnawing feeling in the stomach, headache, etc. Other consequences even more severe are increased blood pressure, heart and pancreas problems, hepatitis and cirrhosis. Nervous system disorders such as lack of attention and tremors may also be part of the scenario.
The liver is the most affected organ because it stores glycogen â€“ our storage of glucose that gives us energy most of the time.
When someone doesnâ€™t eat for long periods, his/her storage becomes exhausted. In this case, the liver synthesizes glucose from muscle proteins. This process becomes difficult to happen in the presence of alcohol because ethanol blocks this action. This is why people who drink alcohol on an empty stomach get affected quicker and this is why excess of alcohol can cause cirrhosis of the liver in the long term.
Enjoy the party! Donâ€™t drink and drive!"

Comment: gymworkouts101 said "-
â–ªï¸Standing Cable Curls
-TARGETS
â–ªï¸Biceps
-
â–ªï¸ Stand up with your torso upright while holding a cable curl bar that is attached to a low pulley. Grab the cable bar at shoulder width and keep the elbows close to the torso. The palm of your hands should be facing up (supinated grip). This will be your starting position. While holding the upper arms stationary, curl the weights while contracting the biceps as you breathe out. Only the forearms should move.Continue the movement until your biceps are fully contracted and the bar is at shoulder level. Hold the contracted position for a second as you squeeze the muscle. Slowly begin to bring the curl bar back to starting position as your breathe in."

Please come out to support. Meet Karen, a registered nurse turned survivor. In 2011, she contracted a devastating case of bacterial meningitis. In order to save her life, doctors had to amputate all 4 of her limbs. Karen suffered a great loss to herself and to her quality of life -- something we all take for granted. In 2013, she was faced with yet another challenge when her brand new $80,000 prosthetic arms were stolen. Even with insurance, Karen still has many illness-related expenses such as modifying her home to be more accessible for her. This will help towards Karen's main goal of getting back her independence. This is something she can't financially handle without the help of the community. The website CaringForKaren.com is dedicated to help offset such expenses. Comment: 305guide said "Many people ask me to indicate a Catholic church in Miami and so I would talk a little about the "Shrine Our Lady of Charity" or rather "Ermita de la Caridad". The church that was built in honor of
Our Lady of Charity of Cobre is one of the invocations of the Virgin Mary, is the area right before Coconut Grove. She, who is the patroness of Cuba, had to be present in a city where the vast majority of its residents are of Cuban origin. And it is interesting to note the similarities with Brazilian culture.
Our Lady of Charity, is also worshiped the syncretic african-Cuban cults like Oshun, the goddess of love and money, freshwater owner. Her day is September 8; on the same day and the day before, they make offerings of all kinds and the festivities are also linked with his sister Yemaya, the goddess of the sea, whose main celebration is precisely the 7th of September. Devotion to Yemanja is very similar to what we see in Brazil.

This is a very well attended Catholic church and has a beautiful view of Biscayne Bay, with a small park that has ambiance music, perfect place to relax and reflect.

If you're Catholic and like to visit churches during your trip, I recommend to stop by here!

Is at:
3609 South Miami Ave
Miami, Fl. 33133"
